# Website sync ‚Äî mirror theory & verification changes into `website/`

The public site in `website/` (Next.js, static, deployed on Vercel) is a
**mirror of the active root documents and the verification suite**. Whenever the
theory or the scripts change, the website must be updated in the **same change**.
Never invent numbers or claims ‚Äî everything on the site is grounded in the
documents and the ledger (the ledger wins on any disagreement).

## What drives the site (data layer)

- `website/lib/papers.ts` ‚Äî the **8 documents** (number 0 = `introduction`, 1 =
  `tfpt_1_architecture_e8`, 2 = `tfpt_2_standard_model`, 3 = `tfpt_3_e8_audit_bootstrap`,
  4 = `tfpt_4_frontier`, 5 = `tfpt_horizon_readouts`, 6 = `origin_theory`,
  7 = `tfpt_research_contracts`): abstract, sections, `keyFormulas`, `highlights`, status.
- `website/lib/predictions.ts` ‚Äî the prediction surface (status = `[I]/[L]/[N]/[P]/[A]` grades).
- `website/lib/glossary.ts` ‚Äî `GlossTerm` vocabulary.
- `website/lib/release.ts` ‚Äî per-PDF version / bytes / SHA-256.
- `website/public/papers/*.pdf` ‚Äî copies of the 8 root PDFs (same filenames).
- `website/public/verification/*.py` ‚Äî copies of `verification/tfpt_constants.py` + **every**
  `vN_*.py`; the in-browser Pyodide reproducer (`lib/pyodide.ts`, `components/Reproducer.tsx`)
  fetches these and runs them client-side.
- `website/components/VerificationDag.tsx` ‚Äî dependency-graph nodes; each node lists the
  `scripts` that verify it + its status marker.
- `website/components/ScriptIndex.tsx` ‚Äî clustered list that must contain **every** script
  (one-line `what`); `TOTAL` auto-counts.
- Status markers also live in `components/StatusPyramid.tsx`, `components/orientation/StatusMatrix.tsx`,
  and the `/verification` marker legend ‚Äî keep them agreeing with the ledger.

## When the verification suite changes (new / renamed / removed `vN_*.py`)

1. Re-copy into the site: `cp verification/tfpt_constants.py verification/v*.py website/public/verification/`.
2. Add/rename the script in `website/components/ScriptIndex.tsx` (correct cluster, concise `what`).
   It mirrors the `introduction.tex` script index ‚Äî list every script, no dangling filenames.
3. If it backs a DAG node, add its filename to that node's `scripts` in `VerificationDag.tsx`.

## When a document changes (content or a recompiled `*.pdf`)

1. Copy the changed root PDF(s) into `website/public/papers/` (same filename).
2. `cd website && npm run release:write` ‚Äî refreshes bytes + SHA-256 in `lib/release.ts`.
3. Update that document's entry in `lib/papers.ts` (abstract / sections / `keyFormulas` /
   `highlights`); update `lib/predictions.ts` / `lib/glossary.ts` if a prediction or term changed.

## When a result or status marker changes

- A marker upgrade/downgrade must propagate to **every** website surface that shows it
  (`VerificationDag.tsx`, `StatusPyramid.tsx`, `orientation/StatusMatrix.tsx`) so markers
  never disagree with the ledger.
- The `introduction` is the reading guide ‚Üí the `/orientation` components mirror its
  before/after, predictions and status card.

## Gate (before done ‚Äî always)

- `cd website && npm run build` must pass (TypeScript + all static pages generated).
- Browser-check the touched page(s): `/`, `/verification`, `/papers/<slug>`, `/orientation`,
  `/falsification`. On `/verification`, click a changed script to confirm the reproducer runs.
- The canonical repo link is `REPO_URL` in `lib/utils.ts`; the Pyodide version is pinned in
  `lib/pyodide.ts`.
